9:
Nice. Your food's always got this
roughing-it-in-the-wild flair to it.
13:
Mm, amazing!
Wait, no. Hot... HOT!
22:
Hate to break it to you, kid, but we're
in the middle of the desert. You want
water, you're gonna have to trek for
miles.
41:
And you're the Hellcat of the Dunes.
Rude moniker, isn't it? I much prefer
Nimbus.
45: How do you know my name?
47:
Oh, Rolan loved telling me stories
about his best friend from the stars.
51:
I miss him too, you know. He was a
beacon of hope. And when he left,
he took that light with him.
58:
You traveled all the way to the west
border, right? How were things there?
62:
Villages are being snuffed out like
candles in the dark. I think the royals
are just getting started.
65:
No... What'll happen to the fields you
created?
67:
I-it's the Hellcat! What's he doing
here?!
71:
Calm down. This is Nimbus. He's my
friend.
75: How are those fields doing anyways?
81:
Follow me. There's something I'd like
you to see.
91:
It's as real as the water you drank
earlier. This brush of mine came
from the ruins. It's magical.
93:
It can locate wellsprings and draw
out water.
99:
That's amazing! You could turn this
desert into a giant oasis.
102:
I wish. The brush controls waterit
doesn't produce it. I could barely
squeeze out enough to irrigate
these fields.
103:
And anyways, I'm a traveler. Neither
me nor the brush ever stay in one
place for long.
107:
...Is it true you two aren't from this
world?
108:
Is there really a place out there
where the soil is fertile and the wind
soft with dew?
124:
Get back! You could've been hurt!
Leave the fighting to me.
142: Yeah. The Hellcat sure can fight...
144:
Rakisha, don't you think... With him
on our side, we could overthrow the
provincial governors... And maybe
even the royal family!
153: No. Insurrection is not the answer.
154:
One governor, sure. We can send
him tumbling off his throne with a
snap of our fingers. But he will
always have a successor. And if this
successor has a taste for
vengeance, what then?
158:
Destruction. The loss of more lives
and more villages. The desert winds
are harsh enough. We don't need
people stirring up a storm.
161:
But even if we don't act, the royals
will! They'll crush us like they
crushed the west!
165:
Is that what this is about? Not
knowing when you're gonna die
scares you, so you figure you'll go
lookin' for death yourself.
168:
You think that's agency? That's
power? It's stupid, is what it is.
179:
He's right. Starting a war will be like
digging your own grave.
180:
We're not killers. We're not fighters.
We're survivors. If, at the end of the
day, we're still alive, we've won.
191:
I'd like to apologize. I shouldn't have
brought you to that village.
195:
*sigh* It's fine. What I expect from
humans around here anyway.
204:
No, I already used the power of the
brush. There's nothing else I can do
for them.
205:
And having a miracle worker living
among them could attract
unwanted attention.
208: Is that why you travel so much?
210:
It's part of the reason. I'm searching
for a new beacon to guide this
kingdom to peace and prosperity.
214:
You didn't get a chance to answer
my question from before. Were
Rolan's stories true?
217: Yeah. We're living them right now.
220:
You might not find what you're
looking for, but... Want to join us?
223:
Thought you'd never ask. My journey
is far from over.
229: Glad to have you aboard, Rakisha.
